                        "The University of Warwick is a true campus university — a self-contained 290-hectare (720-acre) campus on the boundary between Coventry and Warwickshire, with everything (teaching, accommodation, leisure, supermarkets, banks) within walking distance",
                        "Warwick is one of the youngest UK universities (founded 1965) and one of only two UK universities founded after WWII to be in the QS global top 100 — proof that institutional age is not the only path to elite research standing",
