                    vibes: "Warwick is unusual among UK universities because it is fundamentally a campus university — a self-contained, lake-and-woodland environment of 290 hectares that sits in the green belt between Coventry and Warwickshire. The campus itself is the city: 28,000 students live, study, eat, exercise, watch theatre, and socialise within the same green-belt landscape. The Warwick Arts Centre, Warwick Sports Hub, the Oculus learning building, and the WBS Scarman Hall sit five minutes' walk from each other. Coventry as a city — one of the UK's most multicultural — provides the urban counterpoint: the post-war modernist cathedral, the two-tone music heritage, and the rapidly redeveloping Cathedral Quarter. Coventry was the UK City of Culture in 2021 and continues to attract creative-industry investment. The campus is the magnet, but Coventry is the cultural backdrop — and the train station gives you Birmingham in 30 minutes and London in an hour. For students who want a focused, all-in-one campus with global outreach, Warwick is one of the UK's strongest propositions.",
