                    vibes: "Bristol is the most distinctively independent-minded city in southern England — a former trading port that has reinvented itself as the creative, ethical, and sustainable capital of the South West. The city is built on hills around the Avon Gorge, with the university itself perched on the slopes of Park Street and Tyndall Avenue, leading up to the Wills Memorial Building's neo-Gothic tower (visible from much of the city). Bristol's signature feel is part Banksy graffiti, part Brunel engineering, part hot-air balloon festival, part harbourside arts: the Arnolfini gallery, M Shed museum, and SS Great Britain ship-museum sit alongside the Watershed cinema and the Stokes Croft creative quarter. Clifton — the leafy Georgian neighbourhood north of campus — is the iconic Bristol student area, with the Suspension Bridge as its centrepiece. The city is small (~470,000 people), compact, cyclable, and famously friendly. Aardman Animations (Wallace & Gromit) is based here. The BBC Natural History Unit (David Attenborough's documentaries) is filmed here. And Airbus's UK wing factory employs Bristol engineering graduates by the hundred. It is a city for students who want creative, ethical, and engineering depth in one place.",
